Etymology[edit]

From coāgulum +‎ -ō.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /koˈaː.ɡu.loː/, [kɔˈaː.ɡʊ.ɫ̪oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /koˈa.ɡu.lo/, [kɔˈaː.ɡu.lɔ]

Verb[edit]

coāgulō (present infinitive coāgulāre, perfect active coāgulāvī, supine coāgulātum); first conjugation

  1. I curdle; make thick, solid
  2. I coagulate
